key_points: Sean Hannity's show on Fox News Channel was the most-watched cable news show last week.
Hannity's show attracted 3.7 million viewers, slightly ahead of Tucker Carlson Tonight.
Hannity also led in the 25-54 age demographic, with 669,000 viewers.
Tucker Carlson Tonight was a close second in the key demographic with 654,000 viewers.
For the week of August 16 through 22, Fox News Channel had an average total audience of 2.980 million viewers, the highest among cable news networks.
Fox News Channel outperformed not only CNN and MSNBC but also the broadcast networks in prime time.
Other top shows on Fox included The Five, The Ingraham Angle, and Special Report with Bret Baier.
Chris Cuomo's return to CNN's Cuomo Prime Time resulted in a total audience of 1.076 million viewers, a 28% decline.
Cuomo Prime Time also saw a reduction of more than 30% in viewership in the 25-54 age demographic.
CNN experienced a significant drop in women viewers for Cuomo Prime Time, down 30% for the week.
